{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "ac35ab4ed906b88bd3b33d002f2fca2f", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "3. Human Resources Policies", "section": "3.8 Remote & Hybrid Work Policy", "subsection": "3.8.3 Home Office & Ergonomics Requirements", "raw_content": "Employees working remotely are responsible for maintaining a safe, ergonomically appropriate, and professionally suitable home workspace. NexaCorp provides: A one-time Home Office Stipend of $600 for new remote/hybrid employees to purchase ergonomic equipment (chair, desk, monitor, etc.). Receipts must be submitted within 90 days. Annual Equipment Refresh Allowance of $200 for peripherals and consumables. Internet Connectivity Stipend of $75/month for employees in Remote-Domestic or Remote-International arrangements. Access to NexaDesk\u2122 co-working pass: 10 free days/month at any WeWork or partner co-working location globally for employees without a designated office. Employees must complete a Home Workstation Self-Assessment annually and attest that their workspace meets the minimum requirements set out in the Remote Work Safety Checklist (HR-RW-02).", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.8 Remote & Hybrid Work Policy\n            Subsection: 3.8.3 Home Office & Ergonomics Requirements\n            Employees working remotely are responsible for maintaining a safe, ergonomically appropriate, and professionally suitable home workspace. NexaCorp provides: A one-time Home Office Stipend of $600 for new remote/hybrid employees to purchase ergonomic equipment (chair, desk, monitor, etc.). Receipts must be submitted within 90 days. Annual Equipment Refresh Allowance of $200 for peripherals and consumables. Internet Connectivity Stipend of $75/month for employees in Remote-Domestic or Remote-International arrangements. Access to NexaDesk\u2122 co-working pass: 10 free days/month at any WeWork or partner co-working location globally for employees without a designated office. Employees must complete a Home Workstation Self-Assessment annually and attest that their workspace meets the minimum requirements set out in the Remote Work Safety Checklist (HR-RW-02).", "type": "Document"}}